  "market_context": "On the daily chart ETH respected the consequent encroachment of a prior wick and closed back inside the previous day high, signalling a bearish bias for the next day. Intraday price opened above midnight open and daily open, sitting in a premium zone.",
  "key_observation": "Price used midnight open and 8:30 as support/resistance levels: an 8:30 Judas swing ran higher into a series of up-close candles forming a bearish order block, then 9:30 distributed lower to make a new daily low, completing a New York reversal.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily chart, identified bearish bias — price respected the CE of the prior wick and closed inside the previous day high, anticipating a new low next day.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to lower time frame; noted daily open had no upper wick and price was leaving failure swing lows, so a new low was the draw on liquidity.",
    "Step 3: Located price above midnight open while bearish — classified that as premium and anticipated a New York reversal candle (wick-body-wick) forming the high.",
    "Step 4: Watched price trade above daily open and midnight open into a deep premium and form a series of up-close candles, marking that cluster as a bearish order block.",
    "Step 5: Observed price could not close below midnight open, which acted as support/resistance and pushed price back up toward the order block.",
    "Step 6: At 8:30, an opposing run (Judas swing) reached up into the order block, sweeping the high against the anticipated daily order flow.",
    "Step 7: At 9:30, distribution began lower; price returned to the propulsion block paired with midnight open and 8:30, using them as resistance to drive a new low.",
    "Step 8: On the 4H, confirmed the 10:00 candle formed a small high and expanded lower (power of 3), and the 2:00 candle delivered the expected retracement sweep before continuing."
  ],
  "outcome": "Setup played out as anticipated — 8:30 Judas swing into the order block, 9:30 distribution lower, and a new daily low was made.",
  "lessons": "Combine HTF bias (close inside previous day high) with midnight open and 8:30 as intraday support/resistance to anticipate the Judas swing, OB formation, and New York reversal that delivers the daily OHLC.",
